ative to the boat in the opposite direction.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The passenger is stationary relative to the shore because the boat is moving at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"15 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"15 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>15</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m/s</mtext></math></span></span> relative to the water and the passenger is moving at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"15 meters per second\"><math alttext=\"15 meters per second\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>15</mn><mspace width=\"0.2em\"></mspace><mtext>m/s</mtext></math></span></span> in the opposite direction relative to the water.</p>"],"answer":2}]